data.name: Savory Cottage Cheese Crepes
data.quickTastyDescription: Delicate crepes filled with creamy cottage cheese and fresh herbs, perfect for a light yet satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, whisk together the flour, milk, and eggs until smooth to make the batter. Let it rest for about 5 minutes.
Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and melt a little butter in it.

Pour about 1/4 cup of the batter into the skillet, swirling to coat the bottom evenly. Cook for about 2 minutes until the edges begin to lift, then flip and cook for another minute on the other side. Remove from the skillet and repeat with the remaining batter.
In a separate bowl, mix the cottage cheese, chopped spinach, green onions, salt, black pepper, and garlic powder until well combined.
Place a spoonful of the cottage cheese mixture onto each crepe and fold them over. Serve warm.
data.detailedName: Savory Cottage Cheese Crepes with Spinach and Green Onions
data.modifiersForBase: Savory filling with cottage cheese and spinach
